result.execSummary:
Christopher J Collins was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Christopher J Collins was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Christopher J Collins in court with attorney William M. Lennon.  Defendant Christopher J Collins in custody.  Christian A. Gossett appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant does not object to Govenor's Warrant.

Defendant Christopher J Collins in court with attorney William M. Lennon.  Defendant Christopher J Collins in custody, appearing by video conference from the Winnebago County Jail.  Tracy A. Paider appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Extradition hearing scheduled for July 10, 2014 at 09:45 am.

Defendant Christopher J Collins in court with attorney William M Lennon.  Defendant Christopher J Collins in custody.  Adam J Levin appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Conditions:  Do not leave the State of WI;  GPS bracelet shall be in place prior to release and comply with rules.

Defendant Christopher J Collins in court with attorney William M Lennon.  Anthony S Prekop appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant contests extradition and requests Signature Bond.  State argues for cash bond.  Cash bond set.  Extradition hearing scheduled for May 13, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Christopher J Collins in court, in custody.  Anthony Steven Prekop appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Zarling sworn in.  Extradition complaint signed and provided to parties.
